            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Â© 2022 The Author(s) 2022. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved. For permissions, please e-mail: journals.permissions@oup.com.Summary: MeRIPseqPipe is an integrated and automatic pipeline that can provide users a friendly solution to perform in-depth mining of MeRIP-seq data. It integrates many functional analysis modules, range from basic processing to downstream analysis. All the processes are embedded in Nextflow with Docker support, which ensures high reproducibility and scalability of the analysis. MeRIPseqPipe is particularly suitable for analyzing a large number of samples at once with a simple command. The final output directory is structured based on each step and agent. And visualization reports containing various tables and plots are provided as HTML files.",
